Trim the @Iceberg Lettuce{½}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice. Trim the @Carrot{1}, then coarsely grate (no need to peel).

Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Zest and halve the @Lemon{½}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

> If you don't have a microwave, heat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7 for the tortillas.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g} and sliced pepper and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir-fry until the chicken is golden and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, add the lemon juice, @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing and @Chilli Flakes{1%pinch} (add less if you prefer things milder). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the grated carrot and lettuce. Toss to combine, then set aside.

Once the chicken is cooked, add the garlic, @Tomato Puree{30%g} and @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in half the @Mango Chutney{80%g}, toss to coat the chicken, then remove from the heat.

Pile the @Plain Taco Tortillas{4} (2 per person) onto a #plate{}. Heat them through in the #microwave{}, 850W: ~{50%secs} / 750W: ~{1%min}, until warm and soft.

If you're using the #oven{}, pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%mins}.

When ready, share the warmed tortillas between your plates.

Spread a spoonful of the remaining mango chutney in the centre of each, then top with a handful of salad and the curried chicken.

Sprinkle over the lemon zest and remaining chilli flakes if you'd like more heat, then fold over both sides of your wraps.

Serve with the remaining salad alongside. Enjoy!